title: High school football: Riverside Brookfield rebounds against Fenton
text:
High school football: Riverside Brookfield rebounds against Fenton Published: Saturday, Oct. 10, 2015 5:30 a.m. CDT By SUBURBAN LIFE MEDIA 
BENSENVILLE â€“ After suffering its first loss of the season, Riverside Brookfield's football team got back on track with a 25-0 win against Fenton on Oct. 9. 
The Bulldogs (6-1 overall, 2-1 Metro Suburban West) were coming off a 15-7 loss against IC Catholic in a game in which they turned the ball over twice in the late going. 
The win seals a playoff berth for RB, which travels to face Aurora Central Catholic on Oct. 16.
